tasks.description:
Fix string-matching bug in OverlayEditor.tsx drag handler (lines 215-232). The `state.mode.includes('e')` checks run unconditionally after the `move` branch, and `'move'.includes('e')` is `true`, causing every move to also apply east-resize. Fix: wrap lines 219-232 in an `else` block so resize logic only runs when `state.mode !== 'move'`.

File: `src/tools/video-editor/components/PreviewPanel/OverlayEditor.tsx`

Before:
```
if (state.mode === 'move') { nextBounds.x += deltaX; nextBounds.y += deltaY; }
if (state.mode.includes('e')) { ... }  // BUG: fires during move
```
After:
```
if (state.mode === 'move') {
  nextBounds.x += deltaX;
  nextBounds.y += deltaY;
} else {
  if (state.mode.includes('e')) { ... }
  if (state.mode.includes('s')) { ... }
  if (state.mode.includes('w')) { ... }
  if (state.mode.includes('n')) { ... }
}
```

Wire crop into Remotion rendering via CSS clip-path.

File: `src/tools/video-editor/compositions/VisualClip.tsx`

In `getClipBoxStyle` (lines 15-46), after computing the base style, apply crop:
```typescript
const cropTop = clip.cropTop ?? 0;
const cropRight = clip.cropRight ?? 0;
const cropBottom = clip.cropBottom ?? 0;
const cropLeft = clip.cropLeft ?? 0;
if (cropTop || cropRight || cropBottom || cropLeft) {
  style.clipPath = `inset(${cropTop * 100}% ${cropRight * 100}% ${cropBottom * 100}% ${cropLeft * 100}%)`;
}
```

This works for both Remotion preview and final render since `clip-path` is standard CSS. The `inset()` function takes `top right bottom left` order.
